ZCZC OE04
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND
MARITIME AGENCY AT 052300 UTC
ON MONDAY EVENING A LARGE DEEP LOW LIES CENTRED 948 W OF
BAILEY BRINGING GALES OR SEV GALES TO ALL BUT THE FAR S
OF PORTPATRICK WITH STORM FORCE WINDS POSS IN ROCKALL
BAILEY FAEROES AND SE ICELAND. STRG WINDS EXP IN THE FAR
S OF PORTPATRICK. OVERNIGHT MONDAY AND DURING TUESDAY THE
LOW MOVS N AND BEGINS TO FILL CENTRED 958 W OF ICELAND
BY TUESDAY EVENING WHILE HIGH PRESSURE BUILDS IN THE BAY
OF BISCAY. STORM FORCE WINDS AND SEV GALES BEGIN TO EASE
BUT GALES CONTINUE ACROSS MOST OF PORTPATRICK. OVERNIGHT
TUESDAY THE LOW CONTINUES TO FILL. GALES GRADUALLY EASE
IN THE N OF PORTPATRICK BUT A NEW SWATHE OF STRG TO GALE
FORCE WINDS DEVELOPS IN THE S AS HIGH PRESSURE IN THE BAY
OF BISCAY CONTINUES TO BUILD. DURING WEDNESDAY THE SWATHE
OF GALES SPREADS TO COVER ALL OF PORTPATRICK EXCEPT
BAILEY FAEROES AND SE ICELAND. LITTLE CHANGE EXP
OVERNIGHT WEDNESDAY AND DURING THURSDAY.
